---
import { Icon } from 'astro-icon/components';
---
<section class="py-20 border-b border-border">
  <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 text-center">
    <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-primary uppercase tracking-widest mb-8">Trusted by developers moving off PaaS</p>
    
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 max-w-5xl mx-auto text-left">
      <div class="bg-background/80 backdrop-blur-md border border-border p-6 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-4">
          <div class="flex text-yellow-400">
            <Icon name="lucide:star" class="size-4 fill-current" />
            <Icon name="lucide:star" class="size-4 fill-current" />
            <Icon name="lucide:star" class="size-4 fill-current" />
            <Icon name="lucide:star" class="size-4 fill-current" />
            <Icon name="lucide:star" class="size-4 fill-current" />
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground mb-6">"Migrated 15 Heroku apps to a $20 Hetzner instance using Codedock. The zero-config Traefik routing is actual magic."</p>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
          <div class="size-8 rounded-full bg-surface border border-border flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-xs text-foreground">JD</div>
          <div class="text-xs text-muted-foreground">Full-stack Developer</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-background/80 backdrop-blur-md border border-border p-6 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-4">
          <div class="flex text-yellow-400">
            <Icon name="lucide:star" class="size-4 fill-current" />
            <Icon name="lucide:star" class="size-4 fill-current" />
            <Icon name="lucide:star" class="size-4 fill-current" />
            <Icon name="lucide:star" class="size-4 fill-current" />
            <Icon name="lucide:star" class="size-4 fill-current" />
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground mb-6">"Finally, a PaaS alternative that doesn't feel like maintaining Kubernetes. The Yamux tunnel setup is incredibly secure."</p>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
          <div class="size-8 rounded-full bg-surface border border-border flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-xs text-foreground">AS</div>
          <div class="text-xs text-muted-foreground">DevOps Engineer</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-background/80 backdrop-blur-md border border-border p-6 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-4">
          <div class="flex text-yellow-400">
            <Icon name="lucide:star" class="size-4 fill-current" />
            <Icon name="lucide:star" class="size-4 fill-current" />
            <Icon name="lucide:star" class="size-4 fill-current" />
            <Icon name="lucide:star" class="size-4 fill-current" />
            <Icon name="lucide:star" class="size-4 fill-current" />
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground mb-6">"The Canvas view makes onboarding junior devs so easy. They can see exactly how the Redis cache connects to the API."</p>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
          <div class="size-8 rounded-full bg-surface border border-border flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-xs text-foreground">MR</div>
          <div class="text-xs text-muted-foreground">CTO @ Startup</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
